  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, I must weigh several mitigating factors, including the fact that the defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution to the victim. The outburst from the courtroom spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely disproportionate to a first-time, non-violent white-collar offense of this magnitude and has no bearing on this court's decision. Balancing the need for deterrence and accountability with the defendant's potential for rehabilitation and continued restitution, a short period of actual incarceration is deemed appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
